<hr />

<h3>Debates</h3>
<div class="table">
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Preparation</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Set turn order for debate and upcoming month: most EC is first</li>
                <li>move candidate pawns (for free) directly to debate city</li>
                <li>resolve Unprepared and Debate Prep politick actions</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="table-cell tc-6">
            <h4>Debate</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>3 rounds, each participant plays 1 card from hand in each</li>
                <li>play 1 card from hand with a matching debate topic</li>
                <li>skip turn if no cards apply</li>
                <li>add any extra icons, move X steps in that party's direction</li>
                <li>do not refresh hand each round</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="table-row">
        <div class="table-cell tc-12">
            <h4>Reaction</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>for each issue marker, add 1/2/3/5 <i>undecided</i> voters</li>
                <li>refresh hand to 5</li>
                <li><u>Election Day:</u> each party discards 1 exit poll card and 1 state return card</li>
                <li><u>Breaking News:</u> after refreshing hands, shuffle 3 cards into the next deck</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<hr />

<h3>End Game</h3>
<ul>
    <li>most EC votes wins</li>
    <li>tiebreakers:
        <ul>
            <li>party with the majority in the most individual states (regardless of size)</li>
            <li>runoff election, with 3 parties:
                <ul>
                    <li>2 parties tie for most states during tie breaker</li>
                    <li>remove all voters from the party in last place</li>
                    <li>adjust EC and apply tie breaker if necessary</li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>

    <li>if a state has 0 voters from any party, treat as 0-0 tie and EC votes go to tie-breaker party</li>
    <li><u>Election Day:</u>
        <ul>
            <li>after October and all ongoing politick actions (recount, october surprise, etc), parties evaluate exit poll cards</li>
            <li>add voters from the undecided pool</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

